            "summary": "This tutorial is for Chesta version 3.4.1. Download Chesta and unzip the downloaded compressed file to an appropriate folder. The&hellip;",
            "content_html": "<p>This tutorial is for Chesta version 3.4.1.</p>\n<h2>Install</h2>\n<p>Download <a href=\"https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/english.html\">Chesta</a> and unzip the downloaded compressed file to an appropriate folder. The compressed file contains the following files.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\"Chesta3.exe\" (Executable program)</li>\n<li>\"Data File Creation Wizard 3.xls\" (Excel file for data file creation)</li>\n<li>\"Software License Agreement.pdf\"</li>\n<li>\"Sample data\" folder (Contains sample data files)</li>\n<li>\"locale\" folder (Contains ranslation files)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Create a chemical potential diagram using a sample data file</h2>\n<p>1. Run \"Chesta3.exe.\"</p>\n<p>2. Open a data file \"Cl2-Fe-O2-S2 system (1200K).csv\" in the \"Sample data\" folder. The contents of the file are displayed in the Chesta window.</p>\n<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/JustOpenedDataFile-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"675\" height=\"564\" sizes=\"(max-width: 48em) 100vw, 768px\" srcset=\"https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/responsive/JustOpenedDataFile-2-xs.png 300w ,https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/responsive/JustOpenedDataFile-2-sm.png 480w ,https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/responsive/JustOpenedDataFile-2-md.png 768w\"></figure>\n<p>3. Click \"Next,\" and a setup screen appears. You can modify axis assignment and chemical species taken into consideration. For the time being, you may leave them as they are.</p>\n<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/SettingScreen.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"675\" height=\"564\" sizes=\"(max-width: 48em) 100vw, 768px\" srcset=\"https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/responsive/SettingScreen-xs.png 300w ,https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/responsive/SettingScreen-sm.png 480w ,https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/responsive/SettingScreen-md.png 768w\"></figure>\n<p>4. Click \"Next,\" and a new diagram window appears. By dragging the diagram, it can be rotated and viewed from any angle. Various operations can also be performed from another window that is already displayed.</p>\n<div class=\"gallery-wrapper\"><div class=\"gallery\"  data-is-empty=\"false\" data-translation=\"Add images\" data-columns=\"2\">\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/gallery/DiagramWindow.png\" data-size=\"794x610\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/gallery/DiagramWindow-thumbnail.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"720\" height=\"553\"></a></figure>\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/gallery/OperationWindow1.png\" data-size=\"675x564\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/gallery/OperationWindow1-thumbnail.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"675\" height=\"564\"></a></figure>\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/gallery/OperationWindow2-2.png\" data-size=\"675x564\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/gallery/OperationWindow2-2-thumbnail.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"675\" height=\"564\"></a></figure>\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/gallery/OperationWindow3-2.png\" data-size=\"675x564\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/gallery/OperationWindow3-2-thumbnail.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"675\" height=\"564\"></a></figure>\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/gallery/OperationWindow4.png\" data-size=\"675x564\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/3/gallery/OperationWindow4-thumbnail.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"675\" height=\"564\"></a></figure>\n</div></div>",
